# Git & Internationalization — DevClaw

## Git Commits

- All commit messages MUST be in **English**
- Follow Conventional Commits format: `type(scope): description`
- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `docs`, `chore`, `ci`, `test`, `build`
- Scope is optional but recommended: `feat(skills):`, `fix(ui):`, `refactor(agent):`
- Description: imperative mood, lowercase, no period at end
- Body (optional): explain "why", not "what"

### Examples

```
feat(skills): add starter pack with 6 core dev skills
fix(ui): correct toggle alignment on domain page
refactor(agent): extract media enrichment into helper
chore: remove legacy submodule artifacts
```

## Internationalization (i18n)

DevClaw supports three languages:

| Language | Code | Status | Usage |
|----------|------|--------|-------|
| English | `en` | Default | Code, commits, logs, API responses, CLI output |
| Portuguese (BR) | `pt-BR` | Optional | WebUI labels, setup wizard, user-facing messages |
| Spanish | `es` | Optional | WebUI labels, setup wizard, user-facing messages |

### Rules

- **Code**: all identifiers, comments, and logs in English
- **Commits**: always in English
- **WebUI strings**: support all 3 languages via i18n system
- **SKILL.md files**: English (primary), translated versions optional
- **Error messages (API)**: English
- **User-facing UI text**: translatable (default: English)

### When adding UI text

- Use translation keys instead of hardcoded strings when i18n is available
- If i18n is not yet implemented, use English as default with Portuguese as fallback for existing pages
- Keep strings concise — shorter text translates better
